A 28-year-old man drowned at the Midmar Dam in KwaZulu-Natal on Friday afternoon. ER24 members and search and rescue teams were on the scene. According to eyewitnesses, the man who drowned had been under water for over 10 minutes before his body was recovered by the SAPS search and rescue team. He was declared dead on the scene by paramedics. The man was at the dam with his two sisters and friends. The group was there for a swim and not as part of the Midmar Mile event taking place there.